Instruction: With the good 12 V battery installed and all external cables to the PSU still disconnected, use an ohmmeter (power off) to measure resistance between battery + and battery −. Then separately measure resistance from battery + to the LED‑resistor junction node, and from battery − to that same node. This will reveal whether there is an internal short directly across the battery or an unintended hard short of the LED branch to battery − that could also be shorting the PSU outputs and collapsing the LED voltage.
